          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Turn the salmon so it’s skin-side up, then add the <strong>creamy tomato stock</strong> to the pan and cook for a final 5-6 min, or until cooked through</p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p><p>Tear most of the<strong> basil</strong> (save a little for garnish!) into the sauce and give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>creamy sun-dried tomato salmon</strong></p><p>Tip: Add a splash of water if your sauce is looking a little thick!</p>",
